WEBVTT

00:00.093 --> 00:01.296
<i>Previously on "Faking It"...</i>

00:01.298 --> 00:03.309
I want to stay in Austin
'cause my daughter needs me.

00:03.310 --> 00:04.444
I'm not gonna tell Daddy.

00:04.445 --> 00:06.295
This stepsister thing
isn't so bad.

00:06.297 --> 00:07.813
Just stay.
Please stay.

00:07.814 --> 00:08.760
I can't.

00:08.762 --> 00:10.668
I wish I didn't have
to think about this.

00:10.670 --> 00:13.652
I wish I hadn't given you
a reason to.

00:13.653 --> 00:15.087
Can I stay here for a while?

00:15.088 --> 00:16.989
Have you ever had
your heart broken?

00:16.991 --> 00:19.469
Yeah.
There's no magic bullet.

00:20.481 --> 00:23.597
So according to this book,
my love color is teal,

00:23.598 --> 00:25.806
while Liam's is
more of a magenta.

00:25.808 --> 00:27.601
Of course we couldn't
make it work!

00:27.602 --> 00:28.860
What did you get
from your book?

00:28.862 --> 00:32.073
Liam is from Mars,
and you're from Venus?

00:32.073 --> 00:33.506
Thanks for doing this
with me.

00:33.507 --> 00:35.208
That's what best friends
are for.

00:35.209 --> 00:37.374
Just remind me how the hat
helps again.

00:37.376 --> 00:40.214
Now is the time for me
to be figuring out who I am.

00:40.215 --> 00:42.216
Like, I didn't think
that I used to be a hat person,

00:42.217 --> 00:44.652
but maybe I am, and maybe
if I had been a hat person,

00:44.653 --> 00:46.138
I could have made it work
with Liam.

00:46.140 --> 00:49.222
You don't have to be any kind
of person but a Karma person.

00:49.223 --> 00:50.479
So I should probably
lose the hat?

00:50.481 --> 00:51.225
Yeah.

00:51.226 --> 00:53.698
[indistinct chatter]

00:53.700 --> 00:55.962
Mom?

00:55.963 --> 00:56.964
Karma.

00:56.965 --> 00:59.535
Oh, my God, the Karma!

00:59.537 --> 01:02.014
- Wait, no, um...
- Oh, my goodness.

01:02.016 --> 01:04.729
You must be Amy.
We've heard so much about you.

01:04.730 --> 01:07.507
I'm Debbie. This is Jackie.
We're in your mom's PFLAG group.

01:07.508 --> 01:09.745
We were just finalizing plans
for our fund raiser.

01:09.747 --> 01:10.542
It's a hoedown.

01:10.544 --> 01:12.738
Now, Jackie, I thought we agreed
we're calling it a square dance.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.714
Yeah, well, a hoedown
sounds so much more fun,

01:14.715 --> 01:15.705
doesn't it, girls?

01:15.707 --> 01:16.917
Oh, and you two
have to come.

01:16.918 --> 01:18.885
Everyone's dying
to meet you.

01:18.886 --> 01:19.669
- Why?
- Uh...

01:19.671 --> 01:21.787
Well, Molly's told us
all about you.

01:21.788 --> 01:23.623
Karma and Amy,
the out proud

01:23.624 --> 01:25.993
and madly in love
lesbian couple.

01:28.897 --> 01:31.204
I know.
I'm so sorry.

01:31.206 --> 01:33.599
I can't believe you haven't
told PFLAG I'm not a lesbian.

01:33.600 --> 01:35.635
That woman Jackie is gunning
for my presidency,

01:35.636 --> 01:37.203
and her son is actually gay.

01:37.204 --> 01:39.473
If she found out the truth,
she would overthrow me

01:39.474 --> 01:41.474
and keep me from
all the good work I'm doing.

01:41.475 --> 01:43.343
I mean, it's one thing
for you to live a lie,

01:43.344 --> 01:45.479
but you can't make us
live one too.

01:45.480 --> 01:48.623
Yeah, we're really trying
not to do that anymore.

01:48.625 --> 01:49.583
You're right.

01:49.584 --> 01:50.712
I'm gonna meditate on this

01:50.714 --> 01:53.487
and think about what's led me
to this point.

01:54.933 --> 01:57.118
Dad, can you just stop powering
the house for one second?

01:57.120 --> 01:58.308
Don't be mad
at your mother.

01:58.310 --> 01:59.612
I mean, after the year
we've had, you know,

01:59.614 --> 02:02.129
losing the house
and the business,

02:02.130 --> 02:03.839
her PFLAG group is all she has.

02:03.841 --> 02:05.016
Aww.

02:05.018 --> 02:07.136
Molly's been working so hard
on this fund raiser, you know.

02:07.138 --> 02:09.434
It would mean the world to her
if you two would go.

02:09.436 --> 02:11.071
Together.

02:11.072 --> 02:12.054
As a couple.

02:12.056 --> 02:14.173
Dad, do you not see
how insane that is?

02:14.174 --> 02:16.042
- I mean, Amy, do you...
- Yeah, we could do it.

02:16.043 --> 02:16.997
Mm-hmm.

02:16.999 --> 02:18.811
How could you even
consider this?

02:18.812 --> 02:20.780
Well, your mom's always
been there for me,

02:20.781 --> 02:22.361
and if us being
a couple helps her,

02:22.363 --> 02:23.816
then I want to do it.

02:23.817 --> 02:24.869
[sighs]

02:24.871 --> 02:27.354
Yeah, but won't it be weird
for you?

02:27.355 --> 02:29.588
Why would it be weird?

02:29.589 --> 02:31.158
Ohh.

02:31.159 --> 02:32.525
If you're worried
about my feelings,

02:32.526 --> 02:33.861
there's nothing
to worry about.

02:33.862 --> 02:36.797
That's ancient history.

02:36.798 --> 02:38.130
Okay.

02:38.131 --> 02:40.136
Great, then it's not weird
for me.

02:40.138 --> 02:42.303
Let's be lesbians.

02:42.304 --> 02:43.303
Again.

02:43.304 --> 02:46.873
[country music]

02:46.874 --> 02:47.855
Oh!

02:47.857 --> 02:50.183
The guy you just killed
looked just like Duke.

02:50.185 --> 02:51.486
I wonder what he's doing
right now.

02:51.488 --> 02:52.523
I don't know,
working out?

02:52.525 --> 02:54.414
What do you think the odds are
he's wearing a shirt?

02:54.415 --> 02:55.882
- Low, right?
- You are dead.

02:55.884 --> 02:57.761
Oh! Shane, we've been
at this game for two weeks,

02:57.763 --> 02:59.219
and we're so close
to beating it.

02:59.220 --> 03:01.708
Simmer down, it's just a game.
You're obsessed.

03:01.710 --> 03:03.356
I'd rather obsess
over a video game

03:03.357 --> 03:07.243
than obsess over an ex,
like you are.

03:07.245 --> 03:09.431
This one's newish, right?

03:10.998 --> 03:12.231
[gags]

03:12.232 --> 03:14.500
Ugh!

03:14.501 --> 03:16.769
Yeah, I'm the sad one.

03:16.770 --> 03:18.873
You're right.

03:18.874 --> 03:20.874
We used to be Liam and Shane.

03:20.875 --> 03:23.463
We were hookup hunters,
and the world was our prey.

03:23.465 --> 03:24.451
It's time to pick up our spears,

03:24.453 --> 03:25.910
'cause we're gonna get
back on that horse.

03:25.912 --> 03:28.679
I had a horse once.
I loved it, but it ran away.

03:28.681 --> 03:30.217
You're the one that taught me,

03:30.218 --> 03:32.408
the best way to get over someone
is to...

03:32.410 --> 03:33.821
Get back together with them.

03:33.822 --> 03:35.755
No!

03:35.756 --> 03:38.291
[Bleep], you're right.

03:38.292 --> 03:40.726
- We will start tonight.
- Yeah!

03:40.727 --> 03:43.497
Now, I don't want
to rush you,

03:43.498 --> 03:46.099
but Becky's waiting,
and it wasn't easy

03:46.100 --> 03:47.667
getting this appointment.

03:47.668 --> 03:48.956
Maybe we should skip it.

03:48.958 --> 03:50.671
Since she does your hair,
I'd probably just end up

03:50.672 --> 03:51.738
looking like a big whore.

03:51.739 --> 03:52.739
[chokes]

03:52.740 --> 03:54.574
Lauren.

03:54.575 --> 03:56.442
What is wrong with you?

03:56.443 --> 03:59.215
You have not been
yourself lately.

03:59.217 --> 04:00.981
I think I know why.

04:00.982 --> 04:02.004
You do?

04:02.006 --> 04:03.416
Well, yeah,
you're still mad at me

04:03.417 --> 04:06.452
for what we talked about
at the pageant.

04:06.453 --> 04:08.722
Yep.
That's why I'm upset.

04:08.723 --> 04:10.573
(Bruce) Well, it's no reason
to take it out on poor Farrah.

04:10.575 --> 04:12.693
She didn't do anything wrong.

04:12.694 --> 04:14.561
I can't be here anymore.

04:14.562 --> 04:15.595
What in the...

04:15.596 --> 04:17.230
(Amy)
That is too funny.

04:17.231 --> 04:19.266
Oh, God, you're all still here.

04:19.267 --> 04:20.666
We thought you'd be out by now.

04:20.668 --> 04:22.361
We were just gonna
watch some TV.

04:22.363 --> 04:25.206
And then I was gonna leave.

04:25.207 --> 04:27.441
I could do that now.
I'm gonna leave now.

04:27.442 --> 04:28.908
No, Hank, listen.

04:28.909 --> 04:31.481
Hey, nice to finally meet you,
man.

04:31.483 --> 04:33.113
Been telling Farrah
to invite you over.

04:33.115 --> 04:33.799
You free for dinner?

04:33.801 --> 04:35.047
(all)
No.

04:35.048 --> 04:36.984
No, uh, I'm gonna be
with Amy later

04:36.985 --> 04:37.699
at this PFLAG square dance.

04:37.701 --> 04:39.518
(Amy)
Mm-hmm.

04:39.519 --> 04:40.920
What PFLAG square dance?

04:40.921 --> 04:43.290
And who would pee on a flag?

04:43.291 --> 04:45.658
Parents and Friends
of Lesbians and Gays.

04:45.659 --> 04:49.429
So you told your dad
about all of that?

04:49.430 --> 04:51.631
(Amy)
Yeah, and he totally gets it.

04:51.632 --> 04:55.369
It's so nice to have a parent
who supports me for once.

04:55.370 --> 04:58.170
[upbeat music]

04:58.171 --> 04:59.905
Do we have to do anything?

04:59.906 --> 05:01.240
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

05:01.241 --> 05:03.343
The important thing
is that you're here.

05:03.344 --> 05:05.711
And if you're moved to,
you can lend an ear

05:05.712 --> 05:10.549
as people open their hearts
and share their experiences.

05:10.550 --> 05:13.319
- Whoo-hoo!
- Do it, cowboy.

05:13.320 --> 05:15.220
[cheers]

05:15.221 --> 05:17.990
When does
the heart opening start?

05:17.991 --> 05:21.127
- Whoo!
- Jackie?

05:21.128 --> 05:23.230
What is all this?

05:23.231 --> 05:25.198
And what on earth is that?

05:25.199 --> 05:26.966
A human tumbleweed.

05:26.967 --> 05:28.968
[laughs]
Isn't it everything?

05:28.969 --> 05:30.636
You were supposed to run
any changes by me.

05:30.637 --> 05:31.670
I'm the president.

05:31.671 --> 05:33.107
I'm the social chair,

05:33.108 --> 05:36.109
so it is my job
to put on a fabulous event.

05:36.110 --> 05:38.821
It is called a fun raiser
for a reason.

05:38.823 --> 05:40.879
Fund raiser, you forgot the D.

05:40.880 --> 05:42.102
That's a first.

05:42.104 --> 05:44.022
How is this event
supposed to help anyone?

05:44.024 --> 05:47.086
Help them with what?
We should be celebrating.

05:47.087 --> 05:48.320
We got the fun kids.

05:48.322 --> 05:51.478
Oh, speaking of which, you girls
have got to meet my son.

05:51.480 --> 05:53.093
Honey.

05:53.094 --> 05:55.295
This is Shane
and his friend Liam.

05:55.296 --> 05:58.007
This is Karma
and her girlfriend, Amy.

05:58.009 --> 05:59.432
Don't you all go to Hester?

05:59.433 --> 06:00.867
No, no, no, no, no.
They're not...

06:00.868 --> 06:03.238
Friends with us yet.
[laughs]

06:03.240 --> 06:04.972
Let's change that, shall we?

06:04.973 --> 06:08.134
[country music]

06:08.136 --> 06:09.888
I think they have
drama together.

06:09.890 --> 06:11.252
This is not healthy,

06:11.254 --> 06:11.992
and you're talking
to someone

06:11.994 --> 06:13.946
who puts aside time
to smell Duke's old shirts.

06:13.947 --> 06:15.282
Shane, it's fine.

06:15.283 --> 06:16.617
I don't have feelings
for Karma anymore.

06:16.618 --> 06:18.278
They went away
when I fell for Reagan.

06:18.280 --> 06:19.920
You covered them up
when you fell for Reagan.

06:19.921 --> 06:22.155
Now the Regan Band-Aid's off,
and you're pouring salt

06:22.156 --> 06:24.023
into your open,
gaping Karma wound.

06:24.024 --> 06:25.557
Damn her
and her selfish schemes.

06:25.558 --> 06:26.939
It wasn't even my scheme.

06:26.941 --> 06:30.124
Right, so Amy convinced you
to pretend to be a couple again?

06:30.126 --> 06:31.086
- Yes.
- [scoffs]

06:31.088 --> 06:33.699
It was this whole thing
with my mom and her PFLAG group.

06:33.700 --> 06:36.294
And... [sighs]
Can you just not say anything?

06:36.296 --> 06:37.450
I'll do you one better.

06:37.452 --> 06:40.345
I'm pretending
you're not even here.

06:40.347 --> 06:42.398
Why are you even here?

06:42.400 --> 06:43.821
Oh, let me guess.

06:43.823 --> 06:46.104
You and Shane are hitting on
gay guys and their girlfriends.

06:46.106 --> 06:48.982
That's none of your business,
but yes.

06:48.983 --> 06:50.741
Old Liam is back.

06:50.743 --> 06:53.704
Old Amy isn't back,
and to keep it that way,

06:53.706 --> 06:54.888
I have boundaries.

06:54.890 --> 06:57.857
No more romantic speeches,
no more hand holding,

06:57.858 --> 07:01.494
no slow dances, and voila,
no feelings.

07:01.495 --> 07:02.273
♪ ♪

07:02.275 --> 07:06.900
♪ Oh,
she's the best thing that ♪

07:06.901 --> 07:09.410
- What's his deal?
- Being all know-it-all-y.

07:09.412 --> 07:10.476
Yeah, Liam too.

07:10.478 --> 07:14.976
Can we just... ignore them
and be girlfriends?

07:17.937 --> 07:20.280
Yeah!

07:20.281 --> 07:22.949
Who's ready to open
their hearts and minds

07:22.950 --> 07:25.288
in a share circle?

07:25.290 --> 07:29.956
Or you can open your legs and
jump on that mechanical bull.

07:29.957 --> 07:31.193
Oh, but you can't go now

07:31.195 --> 07:34.593
because Karma and Amy
were just about to share.

07:34.594 --> 07:35.672
Aww.

07:35.674 --> 07:36.788
Oh, no, I don't think
anyone wants to hear us.

07:36.790 --> 07:37.847
No, we... we actually
weren't planning on sharing.

07:37.849 --> 07:42.302
But everyone here is dying to
hear your beautiful love story.

07:42.303 --> 07:45.139
Please.

07:48.515 --> 07:51.444
[country music]

07:51.445 --> 07:53.278
♪ ♪

07:53.279 --> 07:55.949
What the [bleep] is this?

07:55.950 --> 08:00.097
It's the PFLAG hoedown.
We're here to support you.

08:00.099 --> 08:03.823
And your sister,
who has two supportive parents.

08:03.824 --> 08:06.604
Where is she, by the way?

08:06.606 --> 08:09.328
I heard you loud and clear
today, baby girl.

08:09.329 --> 08:10.797
You're upset with me,

08:10.798 --> 08:13.167
so I wanted to show you
that I support you.

08:15.913 --> 08:18.704
Every day that I'm with Amy,
I just feel like

08:18.705 --> 08:21.374
the luckiest girl
in the world.

08:21.375 --> 08:25.814
We're not only best friends
and lovers,

08:25.816 --> 08:29.349
but, um, we're soul mates.

08:31.948 --> 08:36.448
I'm sorry, did you say lovers?

08:36.451 --> 08:37.299
Mom?

08:38.645 --> 08:41.178
You two are faking it again?

08:41.179 --> 08:44.212
When I came here to support you,
this isn't what I had in mind.

08:44.214 --> 08:47.718
Please, you only came here
to one-up Dad... it's so obvious.

08:47.719 --> 08:49.587
If he had even bothered
to show up,

08:49.588 --> 08:51.322
I'm sure he would agree
that this charade

08:51.323 --> 08:53.223
is totally unhealthy.

08:53.224 --> 08:55.354
I don't see the harm.

08:55.356 --> 08:57.495
I'm sorry I'm late.

08:57.496 --> 08:59.169
Amy explained everything to me.

08:59.171 --> 09:01.631
See, Dad gets it,
as usual.

09:01.632 --> 09:03.668
Now if you'll excuse me,
my fake girlfriend

09:03.669 --> 09:05.801
is waiting for me.

09:05.802 --> 09:07.929
[sighs]
Fake girlfriends, huh?

09:07.931 --> 09:10.674
I can never keep track
of what these kids are into.

09:10.675 --> 09:13.843
♪ ♪

09:13.844 --> 09:16.146
[cheering]

09:16.147 --> 09:20.184
♪ ♪

09:20.186 --> 09:22.618
Come on, Show Pony.
You love dancing.

09:22.619 --> 09:24.104
And it'd be a great way
for you to meet the people

09:24.106 --> 09:25.254
in your community.

09:25.256 --> 09:28.871
This is not my community,
there is no I in PFLAG.

09:28.873 --> 09:30.615
Actually, they're inclusive
of everyone.

09:30.617 --> 09:33.530
I called the national office.
They're real nice folks.

09:33.531 --> 09:35.232
Hey, how you doing?
I'm Bruce.

09:35.233 --> 09:36.275
This is my daughter, Lauren.

09:36.277 --> 09:38.037
Nice to meet you,
Lauren and Bruce.

09:38.039 --> 09:40.029
Lauren's an intersex.
What's your kid have?

09:40.031 --> 09:41.639
[gasps]

09:41.640 --> 09:44.341
Hon...

09:44.342 --> 09:48.279
But Duke's biggest muscle of all
was his heart.

09:48.280 --> 09:50.448
- Mm-hmm.
- Also his quads.

09:50.449 --> 09:53.586
I'm sorry, I'm just dealing with
some trust issues from an ex.

09:53.588 --> 09:56.687
Can we start over?

09:56.688 --> 09:58.155
We just realized
that we have to go...

09:58.156 --> 10:00.659
- Leave the country.
- Pee.

10:03.026 --> 10:04.376
Did they just rip cord us?

10:04.378 --> 10:05.563
[grunts]

10:05.564 --> 10:06.607
Staying number one
in your class

10:06.609 --> 10:08.899
can't leave a lot
of free time, I know.

10:08.900 --> 10:10.300
I don't see how it would.

10:10.301 --> 10:12.136
On top of that,
you spent spring break

10:12.137 --> 10:14.405
building habitat houses
in Mexico?

10:14.406 --> 10:16.039
My God, Debbie,
it's your favorite song.

10:16.040 --> 10:19.041
Let's go dance.

10:19.042 --> 10:21.011
- Can you believe that?
- I know.

10:21.012 --> 10:23.019
Like you could ever
build a habitat.

10:23.021 --> 10:25.281
[chuckles]

10:25.282 --> 10:27.918
Is my mom proud of me
for anything real?

10:27.919 --> 10:29.683
No wonder I'm so good
at lying about myself.

10:29.685 --> 10:30.684
It's in my DNA.

10:30.686 --> 10:32.656
We can't let our moms
ruin our night.

10:32.657 --> 10:37.060
Let's just forget about
this PFLAG stuff and have fun.

10:37.061 --> 10:39.630
You're right.

10:39.631 --> 10:43.342
And there is something
I've always wanted to try.

10:43.543 --> 10:45.141
[laughter]

10:45.143 --> 10:46.636
This isn't real, right?

10:46.637 --> 10:47.749
Maybe since we're rooming
together,

10:47.751 --> 10:49.872
we've started
sharing nightmares.

10:49.873 --> 10:52.575
Is it just me, or does
that bull remind you of Duke?

10:52.576 --> 10:57.534
Uh, what is my single, handsome
son doing just standing around?

10:57.536 --> 10:59.612
I'm sorry, but Duke is gone.

10:59.614 --> 11:01.718
You just need
to get over that and move on.

11:01.719 --> 11:04.990
And you... what happened
to Liam Booker, teen Lothario?

11:04.992 --> 11:08.313
The 12-year-old that used to hit
on my 18-year-old daughter?

11:08.315 --> 11:09.959
What is the one thing
I always taught you?

11:09.960 --> 11:11.795
The best way
to get over someone is to...

11:11.796 --> 11:13.930
Get under someone else,
Mom, we know.

11:13.931 --> 11:16.367
Ooh, you should get
under that guy.

11:16.368 --> 11:18.153
I guess I...

11:18.155 --> 11:19.636
could give it a shot.

11:19.637 --> 11:22.072
That's it. That's my boy.
You go get him.

11:22.073 --> 11:24.174
Do not talk about Duke.

11:24.175 --> 11:26.823
And if you don't come home
with his phone number,

11:26.825 --> 11:29.880
I'm taking away your Xbox.

11:29.881 --> 11:31.915
All right.
Now let's find someone for you.

11:31.916 --> 11:33.650
Uh, no, no, no,
don't bother.

11:33.651 --> 11:36.120
The Liam Booker
you were talking about?

11:36.121 --> 11:37.622
After Karma and I broke up,

11:37.623 --> 11:40.390
I thought I could go back
to being that guy.

11:40.391 --> 11:41.958
I'm just not him anymore.

11:41.959 --> 11:44.495
Did you say Karma?

11:44.496 --> 11:47.432
[both laughing and cheering]

11:48.666 --> 11:49.666
[both scream]

11:49.667 --> 11:51.072
(all)
Oh.

11:51.074 --> 11:53.570
- Get off me.
- Here, let me help you up.

11:53.571 --> 11:55.409
Sorry I body slammed you.
You okay?

11:55.411 --> 11:56.406
I'm fine.

11:56.407 --> 11:58.074
Ugh, your hair, let me fix it.

11:58.075 --> 11:59.075
Thanks.

11:59.076 --> 12:01.971
[pop music]

12:01.973 --> 12:03.713
(all)
Aww.

12:03.714 --> 12:06.949
Such a cute couple.
You should be proud.

12:06.950 --> 12:10.555
Too bad they're faking it.

12:13.752 --> 12:15.584
Karma, grab your stuff.
We gotta go.

12:15.585 --> 12:16.749
Why, did you tell your friends

12:16.751 --> 12:18.656
that I have a space launch
to get to?

12:18.658 --> 12:20.556
Actually, Jackie knows
you're faking it,

12:20.557 --> 12:22.858
and we gotta leave
before she tells everyone.

12:22.859 --> 12:26.530
What was I thinking?
Lying is wrong.

12:26.531 --> 12:28.798
Why did you tell all
of these people lies about me?

12:28.799 --> 12:31.834
Am I that disappointing?

12:31.835 --> 12:34.566
No, honey, no, no, no.
This is not about you.

12:34.568 --> 12:36.772
This is about me.

12:36.773 --> 12:38.241
[sighs]

12:38.242 --> 12:40.175
I don't know
if you can understand this,

12:40.176 --> 12:43.415
but sometimes I say
and do things that I think

12:43.417 --> 12:45.314
will make people like me.

12:45.315 --> 12:47.216
And I hate that about myself,

12:47.217 --> 12:50.185
that I care so much
about what these people think.

12:50.186 --> 12:52.655
But I don't think
that I can stand to stay here

12:52.656 --> 12:55.525
and watch Jackie
tell everyone that I lied.

12:55.526 --> 12:56.992
It's okay if you want to go,

12:56.993 --> 12:59.657
but, Mom,
if these people only like you

12:59.659 --> 13:01.229
because of something
that isn't real,

13:01.230 --> 13:04.109
then they don't actually
like you.

13:04.111 --> 13:08.100
And they're not worth
all of this.

13:08.102 --> 13:11.607
How did my daughter
get so wise?

13:11.608 --> 13:13.443
By pretending to be
a lesbian.

13:13.444 --> 13:15.479
[both laugh]

13:17.546 --> 13:20.282
Honey, there you are.

13:20.283 --> 13:23.785
Your father and I
are having such a good time.

13:23.786 --> 13:25.322
[laughs]

13:25.323 --> 13:27.857
I'd forgotten
how funny he is.

13:27.858 --> 13:31.059
Look, I'm sorry
I was so quick to judge earlier.

13:31.060 --> 13:34.428
I know how complicated
things can be with a first love.

13:34.430 --> 13:36.087
I just didn't want you
holding on to hope,

13:36.089 --> 13:38.940
like I did with your father.

13:38.942 --> 13:43.772
You know what, it's years later,
and he's finally here.

13:43.773 --> 13:45.275
I mean, for you, I mean.

13:45.276 --> 13:45.992
Mom...

13:45.994 --> 13:51.027
I'm just saying
maybe people really can change.

13:51.029 --> 13:51.586
Oh.

13:51.588 --> 13:53.406
♪ So I fill it ♪

13:53.408 --> 13:58.503
♪ With the ones
I loved and lost ♪

13:59.646 --> 14:02.151
[alternative music]

14:02.153 --> 14:03.659
Lauren?

14:03.660 --> 14:05.263
Hi.
What are you doing here?

14:05.265 --> 14:10.266
My dad thinks I belong here
because I'm... you know.

14:10.267 --> 14:12.526
Here.
Put that on.

14:15.672 --> 14:17.806
He's so clueless.

14:17.807 --> 14:19.793
Farrah's screwing Amy's dad,

14:19.795 --> 14:22.746
and I have to keep it a secret
or else my dad gets hurt.

14:22.747 --> 14:25.415
And then his idea
of supporting me is dragging me

14:25.416 --> 14:29.063
to this PFLAG hoedown
and humiliating me.

14:31.622 --> 14:33.223
What the [bleep]
are you doing?

14:33.224 --> 14:34.632
Okay.

14:34.634 --> 14:37.421
Look, if it makes you
feel any better,

14:37.423 --> 14:38.561
I moved out
a couple weeks ago,

14:38.563 --> 14:40.605
and my parents,
they haven't even called.

14:40.607 --> 14:43.692
They don't know where I am,
and they don't care.

14:43.694 --> 14:46.381
At least your dad's trying.

14:46.383 --> 14:50.839
I can't believe I'm getting
family advice from Liam Booker.

14:50.840 --> 14:52.674
You sure you don't want
to ride the bull?

14:52.675 --> 14:54.944
I shouldn't.
It's a trigger.

14:54.945 --> 14:58.548
Ha, you're funny.
Really funny.

14:58.549 --> 15:01.016
You know, people usually use
humor as a defense mechanism,

15:01.017 --> 15:04.920
so I guess the question is,
what are you defending?

15:04.921 --> 15:06.067
- Uh...
- Uh, wow.

15:06.069 --> 15:07.327
I'm sorry,
that happens sometimes.

15:07.329 --> 15:09.324
My parents are therapists.

15:09.325 --> 15:10.373
Since you brought it up,

15:10.375 --> 15:12.528
I just went through
a terrible breakup,

15:12.530 --> 15:14.598
and I was trying
to make jokes

15:14.599 --> 15:16.866
to keep me from talking
about Duke,

15:16.867 --> 15:18.668
because now that I've started
talking about him,

15:18.670 --> 15:19.935
I'll never stop.

15:19.936 --> 15:21.938
- I should go.
- No, no, wait.

15:21.939 --> 15:24.107
I'm gonna time you.

15:24.108 --> 15:27.385
You have ten minutes
to talk about Duke.

15:27.387 --> 15:30.346
Timer's up, I'm gonna start it
over and talk about my ex.

15:30.347 --> 15:31.393
We just broke up last week,

15:31.395 --> 15:33.750
and I've been overanalyzing
the hell out of it.

15:33.751 --> 15:35.699
But we'll get to that.

15:35.701 --> 15:37.256
And... go.

15:37.258 --> 15:39.588
Uh, okay, don't judge,

15:39.589 --> 15:43.244
but our first kiss
was behind a dumpster.

15:43.246 --> 15:45.306
Where was the second kiss?

15:45.308 --> 15:48.131
[mellow country music]

15:48.132 --> 15:49.347
♪ ♪

15:49.349 --> 15:53.269
♪ I fall ♪

15:53.271 --> 15:58.535
♪ To pieces ♪

15:58.537 --> 15:59.498
♪ Each time ♪

15:59.500 --> 16:02.144
Thanks for saving a dance
for your old man.

16:02.145 --> 16:05.607
I was being too hard on you.
I know you're doing your best.

16:05.609 --> 16:07.732
Listen, when I first found out
about your condition,

16:07.734 --> 16:09.685
you know, your mother
wasn't around to talk to.

16:09.686 --> 16:11.065
I didn't know what to do,

16:11.067 --> 16:12.689
and I was just trying
to protect you.

16:12.690 --> 16:14.022
I thought keeping
this whole thing secret

16:14.023 --> 16:15.372
was a way to do that.

16:15.374 --> 16:17.421
And I was wrong.

16:17.423 --> 16:21.296
I am... I'm proud
of my intersex daughter!

16:21.297 --> 16:22.997
[laughs]

16:22.998 --> 16:24.700
[cheers and applause]

16:24.702 --> 16:26.367
Listen to me,
you'll always be my baby girl.

16:26.368 --> 16:27.602
All right, I love you.

16:27.603 --> 16:31.471
So from now on,
no more secrets.

16:31.473 --> 16:33.642
♪ You walk by ♪

16:33.643 --> 16:37.797
This has been okay, right?
Not too weird?

16:37.799 --> 16:40.841
No, no way.
It's been fun.

16:40.843 --> 16:42.668
It has been fun,
hasn't it?

16:42.670 --> 16:45.394
No boy drama,
no girl drama.

16:45.396 --> 16:47.626
No giant check drama.

16:47.628 --> 16:50.708
Just you and me.

16:50.710 --> 16:53.518
I wish it could always
be like this.

16:53.520 --> 16:56.699
Me too.

16:56.700 --> 16:57.328
[microphone feedback]

16:57.330 --> 16:59.035
Um, excuse me, everyone.

16:59.036 --> 17:02.238
I have an announcement
to make.

17:04.146 --> 17:06.843
My daughter, Karma,

17:06.844 --> 17:08.069
is straight.

17:08.071 --> 17:11.881
[crowd murmuring]

17:11.882 --> 17:13.682
I let you all believe
that she was gay

17:13.683 --> 17:15.984
because I wanted it to be true,

17:15.986 --> 17:19.054
but I have to accept the fact
that my daughter

17:19.055 --> 17:22.873
will never, ever be a lesbian.

17:22.875 --> 17:26.507
But despite this, she has
many other wonderful qualities.

17:26.509 --> 17:29.631
She's kind and caring, creative.

17:29.632 --> 17:32.035
Oh, she has
the most beautiful voice.

17:32.036 --> 17:33.755
Oh, and she was so quick
to potty train.

17:33.757 --> 17:36.205
Mom!
Mom, that's enough, thanks.

17:36.206 --> 17:37.581
Yeah.

17:37.583 --> 17:39.708
I would rather resign my post

17:39.709 --> 17:43.245
than change one single thing
about my daughter.

17:43.246 --> 17:45.614
[applause]

17:45.615 --> 17:47.984
I cannot believe
they're getting off scot-free.

17:47.985 --> 17:49.111
Get used to it.

17:49.113 --> 17:53.421
We're proud to have you
as a friend and president.

17:53.422 --> 17:55.593
Well, that was nice.

17:56.920 --> 18:00.363
♪ Uncover your... ♪

18:00.365 --> 18:01.878
I know, I know.

18:01.880 --> 18:06.387
I want to, I do, I just promised
my kid I'd stick around.

18:06.389 --> 18:08.738
I... I gotta go.

18:10.684 --> 18:11.841
[sighs]

18:11.842 --> 18:12.962
You should take the job.

18:12.964 --> 18:15.215
No.
I promised you.

18:15.217 --> 18:18.981
And I love
having you around,

18:18.982 --> 18:21.047
but it's not good for Mom.

18:21.049 --> 18:22.142
[sighs]

18:22.144 --> 18:24.071
You being here,
all fun and charming,

18:24.073 --> 18:26.020
it just lets her
have hope again.

18:26.021 --> 18:29.762
Hope? Oh, hey.
Your mom does not want me back.

18:29.764 --> 18:31.928
She's always gonna be
in love with you,

18:31.929 --> 18:33.012
and as long
as you're around,

18:33.014 --> 18:36.132
she's just gonna keep
getting sucked back in.

18:38.334 --> 18:40.884
I wanted to be here
for you.

18:40.886 --> 18:43.972
So visit more.

18:43.973 --> 18:47.634
Just call me next time?
No more motel getaways with Mom.

18:47.636 --> 18:50.246
[chuckles]

18:50.247 --> 18:52.849
Come here.

18:52.850 --> 18:54.151
Deal.

18:59.173 --> 19:03.644
Amy, there you are.
Have you seen your father?

19:03.645 --> 19:05.731
[sighs]
He's gone, Mom.

19:05.733 --> 19:07.947
He took the job.

19:07.948 --> 19:10.842
[sighs]
Of course he did.

19:10.844 --> 19:12.785
I'm done lying to my dad.

19:12.786 --> 19:14.387
It wasn't fair of me
to keep this from him,

19:14.388 --> 19:16.489
and it wasn't fair of you
to ask me to.

19:16.491 --> 19:19.358
He deserves to know
the truth.

19:19.359 --> 19:21.963
And he needs to hear it
from you.

19:21.965 --> 19:24.464
There's my family.

19:24.465 --> 19:26.721
I was just talking
to the nicest folks.

19:26.723 --> 19:30.002
Their son's a bisexual.

19:30.003 --> 19:33.040
Bruce, honey?
Would you drive me home?

19:33.041 --> 19:35.644
We need to talk.

19:38.413 --> 19:41.150
[country music]

19:41.152 --> 19:41.824
You know, it's funny.

19:41.826 --> 19:43.916
When I joined PFLAG,
all I really wanted

19:43.917 --> 19:45.734
was to help people
learn and grow.

19:45.736 --> 19:46.242
[phone buzzes]

19:46.244 --> 19:49.462
But the person who really
needed to learn and grow was me.

19:49.464 --> 19:50.121
_

19:50.123 --> 19:51.832
Is that Amy?

19:51.834 --> 19:53.760
Yeah, she had to go.

19:53.761 --> 19:55.928
Oh, you look really bummed
about that.

19:55.929 --> 19:56.996
Are you sure you're straight?

19:56.997 --> 19:59.074
Mom, I am not gay.
Let it go.

19:59.076 --> 20:01.300
Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

20:01.301 --> 20:02.508
And I accept you.

20:02.510 --> 20:03.337
Thank you.

20:03.338 --> 20:06.096
♪ ♪

20:06.098 --> 20:08.613
You know,
I dated a woman in college.

20:08.615 --> 20:09.556
Mom!

20:09.558 --> 20:11.673
Stacy.

20:11.675 --> 20:13.430
She was the gentlest lover.

20:13.432 --> 20:14.947
Keep talking,
and I'm gonna stop dancing.

20:14.948 --> 20:17.885
[laughter]

20:21.487 --> 20:22.621
Ahh!

20:22.622 --> 20:26.393
Sasha, hi.
You're home.

20:26.394 --> 20:28.895
Liam, you've grown.

20:28.896 --> 20:30.906
[both chuckle]

